                                    <p>
                                        The H5N1 virus, known as bird flu, poses serious risks to wildlife, poultry, and
                                        humans. Since 2020, it has spread globally, with rare but severe human cases
                                        linked to infected poultry. The BV-BRC offers the latest data, outbreak maps,
                                        and resources to support research and response efforts. Learn more about the
                                        evolving outbreak and its impact.
                                    </p>
